solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    bool isSubstringPresent(string s) {
        if (s.size() < 2) return false;
        string rev = s;
        reverse(rev.begin(), rev.end());
        for (size_t i = 0; i + 1 < s.size(); ++i) {
            string sub = s.substr(i, 2);
            if (rev.find(sub) != string::npos) return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^2)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Reverse the string once, then check every 2-char substring against the reversed string with a simple find; early exit on first match.

